<h2>Benefits of a Good Night's Sleep</h2>
<p>Getting a good night's sleep is essential for both physical and mental health. Below are some key benefits of quality sleep:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Improved Memory and Concentration</strong>: Adequate sleep enhances memory retention and improves focus and concentration during the day.</li>
    <li><strong>Better Mood and Mental Health</strong>: Good sleep helps regulate mood, reducing stress, anxiety, and the risk of depression.</li>
    <li><strong>Increased Productivity</strong>: A well-rested mind leads to higher energy levels, better decision-making, and improved productivity at work or school.</li>
    <li><strong>Stronger Immune System</strong>: Consistent, quality sleep helps boost your immune system, making you less susceptible to illnesses.</li>
</ul>

<p>Remember, the benefits of a good night's sleep extend far beyond just feeling rested. Prioritize your sleep for a healthier and happier life!</p>